                      <div>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">Dear developers of OpenMPI,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">I am trying to run our
                            parallelized Ftn-95 code on a Linux cluster
                            with OpenMPI-1-10.0 and Intel-16.0.0 Fortran
                            compiler.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">In the code I use the  module
                            MPI  (use MPI-stmts).</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">However I am not able to
                            compile the code, because of compiler error
                            messages like this:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">/src_SPRAY/mpi_wrapper.f90(2065):
                            error #6285: There is no matching specific
                            subroutin for this generic subroutine
                            call.   [MPI_REDUCE]</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">The problem seems for me to be
                            this one:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">The interfaces in the module
                            MPI for the MPI-routines do not accept a
                            send or receive buffer array, which is</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">actually a variable, an array
                            element or a constant (like MPI_IN_PLACE).</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">Example 1:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">     This does not work (gives
                            the compiler error message:      error
                            #6285: There is no matching specific
                            subroutin for this generic subroutine call 
                            )</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">             ivar=123    !
                          </span><span style="font-family:Wingdings"
                            lang="EN-US">ß</span><span lang="EN-US">
                            ivar is an integer variable, not an array</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">         
                            <b>call</b> MPI_BCAST( ivar, 1, MPI_INTEGER,
                            0, MPI_COMM_WORLD), ierr_mpi )    ! </span>
                          <span style="font-family:Wingdings"
                            lang="EN-US">ß</span><span lang="EN-US">-
                            this should work, but is not accepted by the
                            compiler</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">      only this cumbersome
                            workaround works:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">              ivar=123</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">                allocate(
                            iarr(1) )</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">                iarr(1) = ivar</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><b><span
                              lang="EN-US">         call</span></b><span
                            lang="EN-US"> MPI_BCAST( iarr, 1,
                            MPI_INTEGER, 0, MPI_COMM_WORLD, ierr_mpi
                            )    !
                          </span><span style="font-family:Wingdings"
                            lang="EN-US">ß</span><span lang="EN-US">-
                            this workaround works</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">                ivar = iarr(1)
                          </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">                deallocate(
                            iarr(1) )      
                          </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">Example 2:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">     Any call of an MPI-routine
                            with MPI_IN_PLACE does not work, like that
                            coding:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">     
                            <b>if</b>(lmaster) <b>then</b></span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">       
                            <b>call</b> MPI_REDUCE( MPI_IN_PLACE,
                            rbuffarr, nelem, MPI_REAL8, MPI_MAX &amp;   
                            ! </span>
                          <span style="font-family:Wingdings"
                            lang="EN-US">ß</span><span lang="EN-US">-
                            this should work, but is not accepted by the
                            compiler</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">                                    
                                ,0_INT4, MPI_COMM_WORLD, ierr_mpi )</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">     
                            <b>else</b>  ! slaves</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">       
                            <b>call</b> MPI_REDUCE( rbuffarr, rdummyarr,
                            nelem, MPI_REAL8, MPI_MAX &amp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">                       
                            ,0_INT4, MPI_COMM_WORLD, ierr_mpi )</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">     
                            <b>endif</b></span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">    
                          </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">    This results in this
                            compiler error message:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">     
                            /src_SPRAY/mpi_wrapper.f90(2122): error
                            #6285: There is no matching specific
                            subroutine for this generic subroutine
                            call.   [MPI_REDUCE]</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">            call MPI_REDUCE(
                            MPI_IN_PLACE, rbuffarr, nelem, MPI_REAL8,
                            MPI_MAX &amp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">-------------^</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">In our code I observed the bug
                            with MPI_BCAST, MPI_REDUCE, MPI_ALLREDUCE,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">but probably there may be other
                            MPI-routines with the same kind of bug.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">This bug occurred for   
                                                       :  
                              OpenMPI-1.10.0  with Intel-16.0.0</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">In contrast, this bug did NOT
                            occur for:     OpenMPI-1.8.8    with
                            Intel-16.0.0</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">                                                                        
                               OpenMPI-1.8.8    with Intel-15.0.3</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">                              
                                                                         OpenMPI-1.10.0
                             with gfortran-5.2.0</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">Greetings</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"
                          style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span
                            lang="EN-US">Michael Rachner</span><o:p></o:p></p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
